The paper deals with formalizing an RDF graph model and proposes a new graph model for RDF datasets. This involves concepts such as resource path and triple path, and an algorithm for traversing the new graph. The paper also discusses implementations of the graph model, including a new graph engine and an extension of an existing system. These topics are relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including databases (cs.DB), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), deep learning (cs.DL), and software engineering (cs.SE).
